# Fixture rules

- `fixtures/generic-app` is demo input, not the Tell product; keep that attribution clear in `CONTRIBUTIONS.md`.
- The fixture should intentionally trigger the planted genericness tells and drift findings from `BUILD.md`.
- If fixture UI changes, regenerate or update `fixtures/reports/capture.json` and `fixtures/reports/tell-report.json` together.
- Detector expectations must move with fixture/report changes.
- Keep the fixture bland on purpose: Inter/system font, violet-pink gradient, repeated shadows/radii, emoji chrome, centered sections, gray mush.
- Preserve a brutalist or intentional case so taste can mark at least one finding `intentional`.
- The committed report is the offline demo fallback; do not break it while improving live capture.
